cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to predict legislative floor action at the state level. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and its applications. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The use of contextual legislature and legislator derived features suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with political science and lawmaking, which could make cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible category as well.
